documentation.text:
* Network: Kovan
 Aggregator: ETH/USD
 Address: 0x9326BFA02ADD2366b30bacB125260Af641031331
 Aggregator: UNI/USD
 Address: 0xDA5904BdBfB4EF12a3955aEcA103F51dc87c7C39
 @notice : As we do not have data feed for BYX price, we use UNI price instead for exercise purpose.
@dev receive function will emit event in case of ether sent to the contract.
@dev fallback function will emit event in case of bad call of the contract.

@dev Return ETHUSD price
 @return Returns the latest price

@dev Return BYXUSD price
 @return Returns the latest price

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setByxAddr(address).details: to set the adress of BYXUSD pair on chainlink data feed

params._pair: the address of the BYXUSD pair

setEthAddr(address).details: to set the adress of ETHUSD pair on chainlink data feed

params._pair: the address of the ETHUSD pair

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

constructor.notice: * Network: Kovan Aggregator: ETH/USD Address: 0x9326BFA02ADD2366b30bacB125260Af641031331 Aggregator: UNI/USD Address: 0xDA5904BdBfB4EF12a3955aEcA103F51dc87c7C39: As we do not have data feed for BYX price, we use UNI price instead for exercise purpose.

withdraw(uint256).notice: withdraw function. Can only be used by the owner of the contract.
